  • Method Details

    • setTelecomIntegrationMode

      public void setTelecomIntegrationMode(TelecomIntegrationMode mode)
      Request to change Telecom integration mode.
      Note that if you change the mode from system managed the user will need to re-enable Phone Account in settings if you set it back later.
      May throw IllegalStateException on failure to configure service (e.g., if called when app is in background).
      Parameters:
      mode - new mode to set.

    • getTelecomIntegrationMode

      Returns:
      TelecomIntegrationMode

    • isPhoneAccountEnabled

      public boolean isPhoneAccountEnabled()
      Check if PhoneAccount is available.
      For system-managed service value of false indicates that the user needs to enable the phone account in the phone app settings.
      Returns:
      true if PhoneAccount is registered and available.
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if READ_PHONE_STATE permission was not granted by the user

      public void setRingtoneEnabled(boolean enabled)
      Toggles the alert for incoming calls. The alert may include a ringtone, vibration, or be silent based on the phone's settings. Use setRingtone(Uri) to customize ringtone.
      Parameters:
      enabled - true enables alert, false disables it.
      See Also:
